headline: Domino's India operator beats quarterly profit view on strong delivery demand
summary: (Reuters) -Domino's India operator Jubilant Foodworks beat first-quarter profit estimates by a wide margin on Wednesday as lower-priced menu items and free deliveries bolstered demand even as other fast-food franchisees struggled.  The company reported profit of 917.6 million rupees ($10.49 million) for the quarter ended June 30, compared to a year ago profit of 558 million rupees.  Analysts on average were expecting a profit of 645.6 million rupees, according to data compiled by LSEG.

headline: Cava’s traffic growth slows as consumers show reticence
summary: Fast casual segment leaders fell behind some fast food competitors in sales growth this quarter, with Cava the latest to post flat traffic growth.
